Full disclosure: I used to hate my legs. Thought that Id never see muscle definition. Thought that Id always have chunky thunder thighs. But last night while I was BBQing, and unpacking more of my new apartment, I caught a glimpse of myself in the mirror and actually did a double take??. Im currently recovering from my 3rd surgery in 3 years, but all the hard work Ive put in over the last three years since I started my fitness journey haS paid off! ?
.
.
The problem with that statement I said earlier in the quotes and the way I used to think, see and feel about myself was 100% - - ME. .
.
.
We are in control of our bodies. We are in control of what we put into our bodies. We are in control of how we move our bodies. We are in control of believing whether or not we can accomplish something. We are in control of whether or not we believe in ourselves. We are in control of pushing ourselves and challenging ourselves to accomplish things that perhaps scare the shit out of us and goals that may slightly seem far fetched or out of reach. But let me tell you something though, they are only slightly out of reach if you BELIEVE that they are. REACH a little further for them and dont stop until youre satisfied with your accomplishments no matter how long it takes!! Never change the goal, but be flexible with the timeframe it might take to accomplish what you want.????
.
.
.
As soon as Im able to workout again - look out!! Im giving myself a epic transformation for Christmas and Im READY to be OBSESSED!! Are you finally ready to get started with me and get into amazing shape from home? My next Bootcamp starts on June 18th. Youll get all the tools you need - you just need to show up with me everyday and use them ?. 30 min a day is all it takes. 
If I can do it, so can you. 
Shaunna.dunmore@gmail.com

Happy Monday! How was your weekend? ?Have I told you I was invited to 11 weddings this year and attended 8!?? It was a big year for love???????! This weekend was my last wedding of 2017 and it was spectacular!!! It was for one of my best friends from Boston, Katie, and it melted my heart to be able to be with her and her new husband, Bryan in the Outer Banks, North Carolina for their wedding day. Katie and I met 15 years ago in Boston (GASP?) and have stayed so close even though Im in SD now. KAW @kaw3589 I love you and Im SO happy for you and Bryan!! ??????

Having several weddings or events in a year can add up ?and be challenging to find outfits youve not already worn and expensive to buy something new. For Katies wedding I rented this STUNNING @bcbgmaxazria Kauri Gown from Rent the Runway @renttherunway . Have you tried rent the runway?? Its a great resource for dresses for all types of events, jewelry, clutches (and more) that you rent and return 4-8 days later. Ive linked a coupon in my bio for new customers. I actually want to buy this dress, its super classic in black and unique with the cut out and one shoulder look. The State & Willow earrings were perfect for the occasion with the dress (and I also rented them)!

Have a wonderful rest of you day, Im off to Chicago ???to see my family for the last leg of this whirlwind trip! What are you doing this week for the holiday??

Barbora Tomasova, head of Marketing (left), Adnan Raja (middle) and Amelia Ellis (right).

.
Barbora: "Joining the APC team not only enabled me to develop my team working and managing skills but also allowed me to meet and befriend many open-minded people, enthusiastic to explore the future of pharmacy careers together!"
.
Adnan: "I joined APC because I wanted to be part of a team that provides students with countless yet exciting Alternative paths that can be availed with this Pharmacy degree. Hospital, Community and Industry are not the only options."
.
Amelia: "Whilst our degree might feel focused on only a few job roles, there are many more opportunities out there Pharmacy students should know about." .
